{"lemma":"جَرَّ","slug":"جَرَّ","root":"ج.ر.ر","root_slug":"ج-ر-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ج-ر-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":23},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n5378"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AC%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pull, to draw, to drag, to attract"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to extend, to stretch"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to abstract, to rob"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bring about, to cause"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to drive slowly (livestock)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pasture freely (livestock)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to furrow (the ground)","tags":["usually"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to commit a crime or offense"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bear beyond the usual time","tags":["usually"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to wean the foal of a camel (by splitting its tongue)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to put a word in the oblique or genitive case"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pronounce the kasra at the end of a word"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to use the rein"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of جَرَّ (jarra, “to pull”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pulling, pull, drawing, draft"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dragging, drag, towage, hauling"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"stretching, lengthening, extending"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bringing on, causing"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"oblique case, genitive case"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pronunciation of the final consonant with -i"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"foot of a mountain"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"valley"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cave"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Cognate with Hebrew גרר (garár, “drag”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n5378","headword_ar":"جَرَّ","root":"jr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jar~N","text_ar":"جَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jr~r","text_ar":"جرّر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tajoriyrN","text_ar":"تَجْرِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S K) [and app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tajir~apN","text_ar":"تَجِرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said in the TA to be of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tafoEilapN","text_ar":"تَفْعِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljar~u","text_ar":"الجَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], with teshdeed to denote repetition or frequency of the action, or its relation to many objects, or intensiveness; (S;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajtr~","text_ar":"اجترّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AijotiraArN","text_ar":"اِجْتِرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, L, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aijdr~","text_ar":"اِجدرّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AijodiraArN","text_ar":"اِجْدِرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L, K;) in which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"is changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"d","text_ar":"د"},{"kind":"text","text":", though you do not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AijodaraA^a","text_ar":"اِجْدَرَاَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AijotaraA^a","text_ar":"اِجْتَرَاَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", nor"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AijodaraHa","text_ar":"اِجْدَرَحَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AijotaraHa","text_ar":"اِجْتَرَحَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astjr~","text_ar":"استجرّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He dragged, drew, pulled, tugged, strained, extended by drawing"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pulling"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tugging,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stretched,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, L, Msb, K,) a thing, (A,) or a rope, (S, Msb,) and the like. (Msb.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jar~uwA A^a*oyaAlahumo","text_ar":"جَرُّوا اَذْيَالَهُمْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They dragged along their hinder skirts."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~umoHa","text_ar":"الرُّمْحَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AjAr~","text_ar":"اجارّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He dragged,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drew along, the spear."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHadiyva mino A^abaAEidi A^aToraAfihi","text_ar":"الحَدِيثَ مِنْ اَبَاعِدِ اَطْرَافِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN yasotajir~u","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ يَسْتَجِرُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one draws forth talk,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discourse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"news,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, from its most remote sources"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bEd","text_ar":"بعد"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA Al~a*iY jar~aka A_ilaY h`*aA AlA^amori","text_ar":"مَا الَّذِى جَرَّكَ اـِلَى هٰذَا الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What drew thee, led thee, induced thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"caused thee, to do this thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dEw","text_ar":"دعو"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jar~a","text_ar":"جَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jar~N","text_ar":"جَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He drove"},{"kind":"text","text":"(camels and sheep or goats, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gently,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"letting them pasture as they went along."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jar~a AlA_ibila EalaY A^afowaAhihaA","text_ar":"جَرَّ الاـِبِلَ عَلَى اَفْوَاهِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He drove the camels gently, they eating the while."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b3-  [Hence,] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"halum~a jar~FA","text_ar":"هَلُمَّ جَرًّا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"At thine ease."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ElMundhiree explains"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"halhm~a jur~uwA","text_ar":"هَلهمَّ جُرُّوا"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Come ye at your ease;"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljar~u","text_ar":"الجَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in driving camels and sheep or goats, as rendered above. (TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna *aAka EaAma ka*aA wahalum~a jar~FA A_ilaY Alyawomi","text_ar":"كَانَ ذَاكَ عَامَ كَذَا وَهَلُمَّ جَرًّا اـِلَى اليَوْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, * TA) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That was in such a year, and has continued to this day:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA:) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljar~u","text_ar":"الجَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning the act of “ dragging, ” &c.: (TA:) or from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajorarotuhu Ald~ayona","text_ar":"اَجْرَرْتُهُ الدَّيْنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajorarotuhu Alr~umoHa","text_ar":"اَجْرَرْتُهُ الرُّمْحَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jr~A","text_ar":"جرّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is here in the accus. case as an inf. n., or as a denotative of state: but it is disputed whether this expression be classical or postclassical. (TA.) [See also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hlm","text_ar":"هلم"},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jar~a AlA^avara","text_ar":"جَرَّ الاَثَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of a numerous army, means (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It made a continuous track, so that"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it left no distinct footprints,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intervening"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"untrodden"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spaces."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jar~ati Alxayolu AlA^aroDa bisanaAbikihaA","text_ar":"جَرَّتِ الخَيْلُ الاَرْضَ بِسَنَابِكِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The horses furrowed the ground with their hoofs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, A, TA.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jar~a jariyrapF","text_ar":"جَرَّ جَرِيرَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) but the latter form is disallowed by MF as not authorised by usage nor by analogy, (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jar~N","text_ar":"جَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He committed a crime,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an offence for which he should be punished,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an injurious action,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, *) against ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaliY","text_ar":"عَلِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY","text_ar":"اـِلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in the K voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janaY","text_ar":"جَنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) another or others, (S, K,) or himself; (A, K;) [as though"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he drew it"},{"kind":"text","text":"upon the object thereof;] syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janaY jinaAyapF","text_ar":"جَنَى جِنَايَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, TA.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAyaEahu EalaY A^ano laA yajur~a","text_ar":"بَايَعَهُ عَلَى اَنْ لَا يَجُرَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi A_il~aA nafosahu","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ اـِلَّا نَفْسَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He promised,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"swore, allegiance to him on the condition that he should not inflict an injury,"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a punishment, upon him but"},{"kind":"text","text":"for an offence committed by"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"himself;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] i. e., that he should not be punished for the crime of another, of his children or parent or family. (TA.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jar~a AlfaSiyla","text_ar":"جَرَّ الفَصِيلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 4, in two places. ―         -b8-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jar~a AlHarofa fiY AlA_iEoraAbi","text_ar":"جَرَّ الحَرْفَ فِى الاـِعْرَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jar~N","text_ar":"جَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made the"},{"kind":"text","text":"final"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"letter to have kesreh, in inflection; i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xafaDa","text_ar":"خَفَضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.:]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljar~u","text_ar":"الجَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used in the conventional language of the Basrees; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxafoDu","text_ar":"الخَفْضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in that of the Koofees. (Kull p. 145.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jar~N","text_ar":"جَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaruwrN","text_ar":"جَرُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exceeded the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"usual"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time of pregnancy."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a camel)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arrived at the time"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the year"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which she had been covered, and then went beyond it some days without bringing forth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"withheld her fœtus in her womb after the completion of the year, a month, or two months, or forty days only:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA:) Th says that she sometimes withholds her fœtus [beyond the usual time] a month. (TA. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jar~ato","text_ar":"جَرَّتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a mare)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exceeded eleven months and did not foal:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) the more she exceeds the usual term, the stronger is her foal; and the longest time of excess after eleven months is fifteen nights: accord. to AO, the time of a mare's gestation, after she has ceased to be covered, to the time of her foaling, is eleven months; and if she exceed that time at all, they say of her,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~ayolapu","text_ar":"اللَّيْلَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a woman)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went beyond nine months without bringing forth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exceeding that term by four days, or three."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the night,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kbd","text_ar":"كبد"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, long."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kbd","text_ar":"كبد"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jar~a","text_ar":"جَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jar~N","text_ar":"جَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Anjr~","text_ar":"انجرّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a camel)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pastured as he went along:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar. K: [if so, the aor. is contr. to analogy:]) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he rode"},{"kind":"text","text":"a she-camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and let"},{"kind":"text","text":"her"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pasture"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"while going along"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Kudot;.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jar~a Aln~awo'u biAlmakaAni","text_ar":"جَرَّ النَّوْءُ بِالمَكَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nw'","text_ar":"نوء"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"auroral setting or rising of a star or asterism supposed to occasion rain"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"caused lasting rain in the place."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb","L","K","TA"]}]}}